7:41:39 AM [express] POST /api/mealplan 200 in 92811ms :: {"week_summary":"20-year-old moderately active male with Vata-dominant constitution aiming to improve sleep quality, without medical conditions or restrictions, and preferring Indian cuisine within a moderate budget and 1-hour cooking time.","hydration":"Aim for about 2.3–2.5 liters of fluids daily, favoring warm water or herbal infusions; keep a thermos of warm water or fennel-cumin-coriander tea at your desk and sip regularly, especially in the first half of the day.","weekly_strategy":"The week focuses on warm, lightly spiced, and grounding Indian meals rich in complex carbohydrates, healthy fats, and moderate protein to pacify Vata and support stable energy and better sleep. Evenings emphasize easily digestible one-pot dishes, milk-based bedtime-friendly ingredients (like nutmeg and fennel), and an early, lighter dinner. Daytime meals are balanced but avoid overstimulation with excessive chilies, caffeine, or very dry, cold foods to keep the nervous system calm.","clinician_note":"","days":[{"day":1,"day_name":"Monday","meals":{"breakfast":{"dish_name":"Cardamom Banana Suji (Rava) Upma with Vegetables","ingredients":["semolina (suji) 60g","ghee 10g","banana 1 small (80g), sliced","carrot 30g, finely chopped","green peas 30g","curry leaves 4-5","mustard seeds 1/2 tsp","cumin seeds 1/2 tsp","water 250ml","salt to taste","cardamom powder 1/8 tsp"],"portion":"1 plate ~350g","macros":{"protein":"9g","carbs":"63g","fat":"11g","calories":"395 kcal"},"why":"Warm, soft upma with banana and gentle spices grounds Vata and provides steady morning energy without heaviness, helping prevent evening restlessness that can disturb sleep.","substitutions":["Replace semolina with rolled oats for a higher-fiber version.","Use a little coconut oil instead of ghee if preferred."]},"morning_snack":{"dish_name":"Stewed Apple with Fennel and Raisins","ingredients":["apple 1 medium (120g), peeled and sliced","raisins 10g","fennel seeds 1/2 tsp, lightly crushed","ghee 5g","water 50ml","cinnamon powder 1 pinch"],"portion":"1 small bowl ~180g","macros":{"protein":"1g","carbs":"33g","fat":"4g","calories":"170 kcal"},"why":"Warm stewed fruit with fennel soothes digestion and calms Vata, reducing gas and discomfort that can interfere with later sleep.","substitutions":["Swap apple with pear for variety.","Use jaggery (5g) if you prefer slightly sweeter taste."]},"lunch":{"dish_name":"Moong Dal Khichdi with Bottle Gourd and Ghee","ingredients":["white rice 70g","split yellow moong dal 50g","bottle gourd (lauki) 80g, diced","ghee 10g","cumin seeds 1/2 tsp","turmeric powder 1/4 tsp","ginger 1/2 tsp, grated","salt to taste","water 450ml","fresh coriander leaves 1 tbsp, chopped"],"portion":"1 bowl ~400g","macros":{"protein":"18g","carbs":"67g","fat":"11g","calories":"460 kcal"},"why":"Soft, mildly spiced khichdi is ideal for Vata, supporting easy digestion and a calm gut, which is crucial for relaxing the nervous system and improving sleep quality.","substitutions":["Replace bottle gourd with pumpkin or carrots if unavailable.","Use a mix of rice and barley for added variety."]},"evening_snack":{"dish_name":"Warm Spiced Buttermilk with Roasted Chana","ingredients":["thin fresh buttermilk (diluted curd) 200ml","roasted cumin powder 1/4 tsp","salt 1 pinch","fresh coriander leaves 1 tsp, chopped","roasted whole chana (chickpeas) 20g"],"portion":"1 glass buttermilk (200ml) + 1 small katori chana (20g)","macros":{"protein":"7g","carbs":"13g","fat":"3g","calories":"110 kcal"},"why":"Lightly spiced warm buttermilk supports digestion in the late afternoon while keeping Vata grounded; a small amount of roasted chana provides protein without heaviness before dinner.","substitutions":["Replace buttermilk with warm herbal tea if you are sensitive to dairy.","Swap roasted chana with a small handful of soaked then drained almonds (10g)."]},"dinner":{"dish_name":"Soft Phulka with Masoor Dal and Carrot-Beans Subzi","ingredients":["whole wheat flour 60g","water for dough 30ml","ghee 5g (for brushing)","split red masoor dal 45g","carrot 40g, chopped","French beans 40g, chopped","onion 20g, chopped","tomato 30g, chopped","cumin seeds 1/2 tsp","turmeric powder 1/4 tsp","coriander powder 1/2 tsp","ghee 5g for cooking dal and subzi","salt to taste","water 300ml"],"portion":"2 small phulkas (~60g flour total) + 1 bowl dal (200g) + 1 small katori subzi (100g)","macros":{"protein":"20g","carbs":"70g","fat":"12g","calories":"480 kcal"},"why":"An early, light but satisfying dinner with soft grains and well-cooked dal calms Vata and avoids heaviness at night, supporting deeper sleep.","substitutions":["Replace masoor dal with moong dal if you want an even lighter option.","Swap phulka with soft jeera rice (100g cooked) on days you prefer rice."]}}},{"day":2,"day_name":"Tuesday","meals":{"breakfast":{"dish_name":"Warm Cardamom Oats Porridge with Dates and Nuts","ingredients":["rolled oats 50g","milk 200ml","water 50ml","dates 2 pieces (15g), chopped","almonds 5 pieces (6g), soaked and sliced","ghee 5g","cardamom powder 1/8 tsp"],"portion":"1 bowl ~300g","macros":{"protein":"11g","carbs":"48g","fat":"13g","calories":"370 kcal"},"why":"Warm, creamy porridge with healthy fats steadies Vata and provides slow-release energy, reducing evening fatigue and irritability that can disrupt sleep.","substitutions":["Use lactose-free milk or almond milk if needed.","Replace dates with figs or raisins for variety."]},"morning_snack":{"dish_name":"Fresh Papaya with Lime","ingredients":["papaya 150g, cubed","fresh lime juice 1 tsp"],"portion":"1 small bowl ~160g","macros":{"protein":"1g","carbs":"18g","fat":"0g","calories":"70 kcal"},"why":"Ripe papaya is soothing for digestion and gentle for Vata, helping maintain a light, comfortable stomach through the day to support restful sleep at night.","substitutions":["Replace papaya with ripe mango in season.","Add a pinch of roasted cumin powder if you prefer a savory touch."]},"lunch":{"dish_name":"Jeera Rice with Toor Dal Tadka and Pumpkin Subzi","ingredients":["white rice 75g","ghee 5g (for rice)","cumin seeds 1/2 tsp","toor dal 50g","onion 20g, chopped","tomato 30g, chopped","garlic 1 clove, minced","turmeric 1/4 tsp","mustard seeds 1/2 tsp","ghee 5g (for dal tadka)","pumpkin 100g, cubed","curry leaves 5-6","salt to taste","water 450ml"],"portion":"1 plate ~400g (rice 150g cooked + dal 150g + subzi 100g)","macros":{"protein":"17g","carbs":"77g","fat":"13g","calories":"490 kcal"},"why":"Mild jeera rice and ghee-rich dal with sweet pumpkin create a grounding, comforting meal that nourishes Vata and prevents the late-afternoon crashes that interfere with night-time relaxation.","substitutions":["Replace pumpkin with bottle gourd or sweet potato.","Use masoor dal instead of toor dal for quicker cooking."]},"evening_snack":{"dish_name":"Warm Fennel-Coriander Herbal Tea with Banana","ingredients":["water 250ml","fennel seeds 1/2 tsp","coriander seeds 1/2 tsp","small banana 1 (80g)"],"portion":"1 cup tea (200–250ml) + 1 banana","macros":{"protein":"1g","carbs":"21g","fat":"0g","calories":"85 kcal"},"why":"A mild digestive tea plus banana stabilizes blood sugar and calms digestion, which helps wind down the nervous system and supports falling asleep more easily later.","substitutions":["Add a few crushed cardamom pods instead of coriander if preferred.","Swap banana with 2 soaked dates if you eat dinner soon after."]},"dinner":{"dish_name":"Vegetable Dalia Khichdi with Peas and Carrot","ingredients":["broken wheat (dalia) 70g","split moong dal 30g","green peas 30g","carrot 40g, diced","ginger 1/2 tsp, grated","cumin seeds 1/2 tsp","turmeric powder 1/4 tsp","ghee 10g","salt to taste","water 400ml","fresh coriander leaves 1 tbsp, chopped"],"portion":"1 bowl ~380g","macros":{"protein":"16g","carbs":"67g","fat":"11g","calories":"430 kcal"},"why":"Soft, one-pot dalia khichdi is Vata-pacifying and easy to digest in the evening, providing satiety without heaviness so your body can focus on repair and deep sleep.","substitutions":["Replace dalia with quinoa or barley for variety.","Use a mix of bottle gourd and beans instead of peas and carrot."]}}},{"day":3,"day_name":"Wednesday","meals":{"breakfast":{"dish_name":"Besan Chilla Stuffed with Paneer and Spinach","ingredients":["besan (gram flour) 60g","water 70ml","paneer 40g, crumbled","spinach 30g, finely chopped","onion 20g, finely chopped","cumin seeds 1/2 tsp","turmeric 1/4 tsp","ghee 5g for cooking","salt to taste","fresh coriander leaves 1 tbsp, chopped"],"portion":"2 medium chillas ~250g","macros":{"protein":"17g","carbs":"25g","fat":"12g","calories":"310 kcal"},"why":"Warm, soft chillas with paneer provide grounding protein and fats without being too heavy, preventing mid-morning crashes and stabilizing Vata for better night-time calm.","substitutions":["Replace paneer with grated boiled potato for a lighter stuffing.","Use moong dal batter instead of besan for variation."]},"morning_snack":{"dish_name":"Guava Slices with Black Salt and Fennel","ingredients":["guava 120g, sliced and de-seeded if hard","black salt 1 pinch","fennel seeds 1/4 tsp, lightly crushed"],"portion":"1 small plate ~130g","macros":{"protein":"2g","carbs":"17g","fat":"0g","calories":"70 kcal"},"why":"Guava with fennel is light yet vitamin-rich; the mild digestive spices keep Vata digestion balanced without overstimulation.","substitutions":["Replace guava with orange segments.","Skip black salt if you are limiting sodium and use plain roasted cumin instead."]},"lunch":{"dish_name":"Quinoa Pulao with Mixed Vegetables and Moong Sprouts","ingredients":["quinoa 70g, rinsed","moong sprouts 30g (lightly steamed)","carrot 30g, diced","green beans 30g, chopped","peas 30g","onion 30g, sliced","ghee 10g","cumin seeds 1/2 tsp","bay leaf 1","turmeric 1/4 tsp","salt to taste","water 200ml","fresh coriander leaves 1 tbsp"],"portion":"1 plate ~350g","macros":{"protein":"15g","carbs":"60g","fat":"11g","calories":"420 kcal"},"why":"Quinoa offers complete protein while warm, moist cooking and ghee make it Vata-friendly, sustaining energy gently through the afternoon.","substitutions":["Replace quinoa with brown rice or jowar grains.","Use lightly cooked lentils instead of sprouts if you prefer softer texture."]},"evening_snack":{"dish_name":"Masala Jaggery Milk with Nutmeg (Early Evening)","ingredients":["milk 200ml","water 30ml","jaggery powder 5g (added after slight cooling)","nutmeg powder 1/16 tsp (a pinch)","cardamom powder 1/8 tsp"],"portion":"1 cup ~220ml","macros":{"protein":"6g","carbs":"15g","fat":"7g","calories":"150 kcal"},"why":"Warm milk with nutmeg and cardamom is classic for Vata and directly supports relaxation and sleep onset when taken in early evening.","substitutions":["Use lactose-free milk if you are sensitive.","Replace jaggery with a small amount of honey added only when milk is lukewarm."]},"dinner":{"dish_name":"Soft Idli with Mild Sambar and Coconut-Coriander Chutney","ingredients":["idli batter (rice + urad dal fermented) 150g (for ~4 small idlis)","toor dal 30g for sambar","drumstick pieces 40g","bottle gourd or pumpkin 40g, cubed","tomato 20g, chopped","tamarind pulp 1 tsp (mild)","sambar powder 1 tsp (low chili)","ghee 5g for tempering","mustard seeds 1/2 tsp","curry leaves 6-8","grated fresh coconut 15g","fresh coriander leaves 10g","green chili 1/4 piece (optional, very mild)","salt to taste","water 350ml"],"portion":"4 small idlis (~160g) + 1 bowl sambar (160g) + 2 tbsp chutney (30g)","macros":{"protein":"15g","carbs":"67g","fat":"12g","calories":"430 kcal"},"why":"Soft, fermented, and warm south Indian dinner is gentle on digestion and the nervous system, fitting Vata needs and supporting sleep by avoiding heaviness.","substitutions":["Replace sambar with simple moong dal if you want even milder spices.","Use rice dosa instead of idli if you prefer a crisp yet still light option."]}}},{"day":4,"day_name":"Thursday","meals":{"breakfast":{"dish_name":"Sweet Potato Poha with Peas and Curry Leaves","ingredients":["thick poha (flattened rice) 60g","sweet potato 80g, boiled and cubed","green peas 20g","onion 20g, chopped","curry leaves 6-8","mustard seeds 1/2 tsp","turmeric 1/4 tsp","ghee 10g","salt to taste","lemon juice 1 tsp","fresh coriander leaves 1 tbsp, chopped"],"portion":"1 plate ~320g","macros":{"protein":"7g","carbs":"63g","fat":"11g","calories":"390 kcal"},"why":"Warm, soft poha with sweet potato offers grounding complex carbs ideal for Vata, stabilizing energy and mood across the day for better sleep later.","substitutions":["Replace sweet potato with regular potato if needed.","Use peanuts (10g) instead of peas for crunch if tolerated."]},"morning_snack":{"dish_name":"Orange and Pomegranate Bowl","ingredients":["orange segments 80g","pomegranate seeds 50g"],"portion":"1 small bowl ~130g","macros":{"protein":"2g","carbs":"26g","fat":"0g","calories":"110 kcal"},"why":"Juicy fruits hydrate and provide antioxidants without heaviness, supporting overall recovery and nervous system health linked to sleep.","substitutions":["Replace orange with sweet lime (mosambi).","Add a few soaked raisins (10g) in cooler weather for extra sweetness."]},"lunch":{"dish_name":"Barley and Moong Dal Khichdi with Carrot and Beet","ingredients":["pearled barley 60g","split yellow moong dal 40g","carrot 40g, diced","beetroot 30g, diced","ghee 10g","cumin seeds 1/2 tsp","ginger 1/2 tsp, grated","turmeric 1/4 tsp","salt to taste","water 450ml","fresh coriander leaves 1 tbsp"],"portion":"1 bowl ~380g","macros":{"protein":"16g","carbs":"64g","fat":"11g","calories":"420 kcal"},"why":"This slightly heavier but still soft khichdi grounds Vata and offers minerals and complex carbs that keep you satiated and calm through the afternoon.","substitutions":["Replace barley with brown rice if preferred.","Use pumpkin instead of beetroot if you want a milder flavor."]},"evening_snack":{"dish_name":"Light Vegetable Soup with Carrot and Bottle Gourd","ingredients":["carrot 40g, sliced","bottle gourd 40g, diced","tomato 20g, chopped","ghee 5g","cumin seeds 1/2 tsp","black pepper 1 pinch","salt to taste","water 250ml","fresh coriander leaves 1 tbsp"],"portion":"1 bowl ~250ml","macros":{"protein":"2g","carbs":"10g","fat":"5g","calories":"90 kcal"},"why":"Warm, light soup in the early evening calms Vata and prepares the digestive system for a modest dinner, indirectly supporting smoother sleep.","substitutions":["Replace bottle gourd with zucchini.","Add a spoon of cooked moong dal for a bit more protein."]},"dinner":{"dish_name":"Soft Rice with Urad Dal Curry and Okra Stir-fry","ingredients":["white rice 70g","ghee 5g","split urad dal 40g","onion 20g, chopped","tomato 30g, chopped","ginger 1/2 tsp, grated","cumin seeds 1/2 tsp","turmeric 1/4 tsp","ghee 5g (for dal)","okra (bhindi) 80g, sliced","mustard seeds 1/2 tsp","curry leaves 6","sesame oil or ghee 5g (for okra)","salt to taste","water 350ml"],"portion":"1 plate ~400g (rice 150g cooked + dal 150g + okra 100g)","macros":{"protein":"19g","carbs":"70g","fat":"14g","calories":"480 kcal"},"why":"Soft rice with well-cooked urad and okra is grounding and oily enough to pacify Vata, while still moderate in portion so sleep is not disturbed.","substitutions":["Replace urad dal with moong dal if you find urad heavy.","Swap okra with a simple carrot-beans stir-fry if desired."]}}},{"day":5,"day_name":"Friday","meals":{"breakfast":{"dish_name":"Rice Flour Idiyappam with Coconut Milk and Jaggery","ingredients":["rice flour 70g","hot water 80ml (for dough)","salt 1 pinch","thin coconut milk 80ml","warm milk 60ml","jaggery powder 8g","cardamom powder 1/8 tsp"],"portion":"1 plate ~250g (idiyappam + sweet milk mix)","macros":{"protein":"5g","carbs":"62g","fat":"7g","calories":"340 kcal"},"why":"Soft, warm and slightly sweet, this breakfast is very calming for Vata and offers quick yet gentle energy to start the day without overstimulating the nervous system.","substitutions":["Use only cow’s milk instead of coconut milk if preferred.","Replace idiyappam with plain idli if you lack an idiyappam press."]},"morning_snack":{"dish_name":"Mixed Fruit Bowl with Banana, Mango and Amla","ingredients":["banana 1 small (80g), sliced","ripe mango 60g, diced","fresh amla 10g, finely chopped or grated","honey 1/2 tsp (optional)"],"portion":"1 bowl ~160g","macros":{"protein":"2g","carbs":"37g","fat":"0g","calories":"150 kcal"},"why":"This sweet, vitamin C-rich mix supports immunity and tissue repair, both important for sleep quality, while banana and mango ground Vata.","substitutions":["Replace mango with papaya when not in season.","Use a dash of rock salt instead of honey if you prefer less sweetness."]},"lunch":{"dish_name":"Bajra Roti with Moong Dal Fry and Lauki Raita","ingredients":["bajra flour 60g","wheat flour 15g (to help binding)","warm water 40ml","ghee 5g (for roti)","split yellow moong dal 45g","onion 20g, chopped","tomato 20g, chopped","cumin seeds 1/2 tsp","turmeric 1/4 tsp","ghee 5g (for dal)","bottle gourd 40g, grated and lightly steamed","curd 80g","roasted cumin powder 1/4 tsp","salt to taste","water 250ml for dal"],"portion":"2 small bajra rotis (~75g flour total) + 1 bowl dal (160g) + 1 katori raita (100g)","macros":{"protein":"18g","carbs":"65g","fat":"12g","calories":"440 kcal"},"why":"Bajra is warming and grounding for Vata, and combined with soft moong dal and cooling lauki raita it offers stable energy without digestive strain.","substitutions":["Replace bajra with jowar flour if preferred.","Use cucumber instead of lauki in raita."]},"evening_snack":{"dish_name":"Roasted Sweet Potato Chaat (Very Mild)","ingredients":["sweet potato 100g, boiled and cubed","ghee 3g","cumin powder 1/4 tsp","black salt 1 pinch","lemon juice 1 tsp","fresh coriander leaves 1 tbsp, chopped"],"portion":"1 small plate ~120g","macros":{"protein":"2g","carbs":"24g","fat":"3g","calories":"130 kcal"},"why":"Warm sweet potato is an excellent Vata-pacifying snack, giving a gentle carb boost in the evening to prevent late-night hunger that can disturb sleep.","substitutions":["Replace sweet potato with boiled beetroot for variety.","Use olive oil instead of ghee if desired."]},"dinner":{"dish_name":"Soft Vegetable Pongal with Moong Dal and Black Pepper","ingredients":["raw rice 70g","split yellow moong dal 40g","bottle gourd 40g, finely chopped","carrot 30g, chopped","ginger 1/2 tsp, grated","cumin seeds 1/2 tsp","crushed black pepper 1/8 tsp","ghee 10g","curry leaves 6-8","cashews 6 halves (6g), lightly roasted (optional)","salt to taste","water 450ml"],"portion":"1 bowl ~380g","macros":{"protein":"16g","carbs":"64g","fat":"13g","calories":"440 kcal"},"why":"Soft, ghee-rich pongal is a classic Vata-soothing dinner that is very easy to digest and promotes a warm, relaxed feeling before bed.","substitutions":["Replace rice with broken wheat if you prefer a nuttier texture.","Skip cashews if you want it lighter at night."]}}},{"day":6,"day_name":"Saturday","meals":{"breakfast":{"dish_name":"Vegetable Semolina Idli with Coconut Chutney","ingredients":["semolina (suji) 70g","curd 70g","water 40ml","carrot 20g, grated","green peas 15g","salt to taste","eno or baking soda 1/4 tsp","ghee 5g (for greasing)","grated coconut 15g","fresh coriander leaves 10g","ginger 1/2 tsp","green chili 1/4 (optional, mild)","salt for chutney","water 20ml for chutney"],"portion":"4 small idlis (~180g) + 2 tbsp chutney (~30g)","macros":{"protein":"10g","carbs":"47g","fat":"11g","calories":"340 kcal"},"why":"Soft, warm idlis are gentle on Vata, and the coconut chutney adds healthy fats that support satiety and nervous system health.","substitutions":["Replace semolina with idli rice batter if you prefer fermented foods.","Use roasted chana dal instead of coconut for a lighter chutney."]},"morning_snack":{"dish_name":"Buttermilk with Roasted Methi Seeds","ingredients":["thin buttermilk 200ml","roasted methi (fenugreek) seeds 1/4 tsp, lightly crushed","roasted cumin powder 1/4 tsp","salt 1 pinch","fresh coriander leaves 1 tsp, chopped"],"portion":"1 glass ~200ml","macros":{"protein":"3g","carbs":"6g","fat":"2g","calories":"50 kcal"},"why":"Fenugreek in buttermilk gently supports digestion and blood sugar balance, which indirectly supports more stable energy and better sleep at night.","substitutions":["Skip methi if you dislike bitterness and use only cumin.","Replace buttermilk with warm herbal tea on colder days."]},"lunch":{"dish_name":"Rajma Chawal (Light Version) with Beetroot Salad","ingredients":["white rice 75g","ghee 5g (for rice)","rajma (kidney beans) 50g, soaked overnight and cooked","onion 30g, chopped","tomato 40g, chopped","ginger-garlic paste 1 tsp","cumin seeds 1/2 tsp","turmeric 1/4 tsp","coriander powder 1/2 tsp","garam masala 1/4 tsp (very mild)","ghee 5g (for rajma)","beetroot 40g, boiled and cubed","carrot 30g, grated","lemon juice 1 tsp","salt to taste","fresh coriander leaves 1 tbsp","water 250ml"],"portion":"1 plate ~420g (rice 150g cooked + rajma 170g + salad 100g)","macros":{"protein":"19g","carbs":"82g","fat":"13g","calories":"520 kcal"},"why":"This lighter rajma chawal provides satisfying comfort and iron-rich beans, while a moderate portion and added salad keep it digestible for Vata.","substitutions":["Replace rajma with chana (chickpeas) if preferred.","Use brown rice instead of white for more fiber if your digestion handles it well."]},"evening_snack":{"dish_name":"Warm Haldi Doodh (Golden Milk) with Black Pepper","ingredients":["milk 200ml","turmeric powder 1/4 tsp","black pepper powder 1 pinch","ghee 1/2 tsp or 1 tsp coconut oil","jaggery powder 5g (added after cooling slightly)"],"portion":"1 cup ~220ml","macros":{"protein":"6g","carbs":"15g","fat":"8g","calories":"160 kcal"},"why":"Turmeric milk is calming and anti-inflammatory, and the warm, slightly fatty drink in early evening soothes Vata and promotes drowsiness later.","substitutions":["Use almond milk if you avoid dairy.","Replace jaggery with a small amount of honey added only when lukewarm."]},"dinner":{"dish_name":"Vegetable Oats Khichdi with Peas and Bottle Gourd","ingredients":["rolled oats 60g","split yellow moong dal 30g","bottle gourd 50g, diced","green peas 25g","carrot 30g, diced","ginger 1/2 tsp, grated","cumin seeds 1/2 tsp","turmeric 1/4 tsp","ghee 10g","salt to taste","water 400ml","fresh coriander leaves 1 tbsp"],"portion":"1 bowl ~360g","macros":{"protein":"15g","carbs":"56g","fat":"11g","calories":"390 kcal"},"why":"Oats khichdi is a soft, warm, and nourishing one-pot dinner perfect for Vata, promoting easy digestion and a calm body before sleep.","substitutions":["Replace oats with rice flakes (poha) for different texture.","Use pumpkin instead of bottle gourd in colder weather."]}}},{"day":7,"day_name":"Sunday","meals":{"breakfast":{"dish_name":"Stuffed Aloo Paratha with Curd","ingredients":["whole wheat flour 70g","water for dough 35ml","boiled potato 80g, mashed","coriander leaves 1 tbsp, chopped","cumin powder 1/4 tsp","ajwain (carom) seeds 1/4 tsp","ghee 10g (for cooking)","salt to taste","curd 80g (served on side)"],"portion":"1 large paratha (~200g) + 1 katori curd (80g)","macros":{"protein":"11g","carbs":"63g","fat":"15g","calories":"470 kcal"},"why":"A comforting Sunday breakfast that's grounding and Vata-pacifying when cooked with ghee and served with curd, best eaten a bit later in the morning.","substitutions":["Replace potato with a mix of potato and grated carrot for lighter filling.","Use ragi-wheat mix flour for a different grain profile."]},"morning_snack":{"dish_name":"Coconut Water with Tender Coconut Malai","ingredients":["fresh coconut water 200ml","tender coconut malai 30g"],"portion":"1 glass ~200ml + malai ~30g","macros":{"protein":"1g","carbs":"11g","fat":"3g","calories":"80 kcal"},"why":"Hydrating and mildly sweet, coconut water with malai is gentle on Vata and supports electrolyte balance, especially useful on a more relaxed day.","substitutions":["Replace with warm lemon water if coconut water is unavailable.","Skip malai if you want fewer calories."]},"lunch":{"dish_name":"Vegetable Pulao with Curd Raita","ingredients":["basmati rice 75g","carrot 30g, diced","peas 25g","beans 25g, chopped","onion 30g, sliced","ghee 10g","cumin seeds 1/2 tsp","bay leaf 1","cloves 2","cinnamon small piece","salt to taste","water 200ml","curd 100g","cucumber 30g, grated","roasted cumin powder 1/4 tsp","fresh coriander leaves 1 tbsp"],"portion":"1 plate ~400g (pulao 250g + raita 120g)","macros":{"protein":"14g","carbs":"74g","fat":"14g","calories":"480 kcal"},"why":"Mildly spiced, ghee-based pulao with raita is satisfying yet not overly heavy, helping keep Vata content while allowing space for an early, lighter dinner for better sleep.","substitutions":["Replace basmati with short-grain rice if preferred.","Use boondi raita instead of cucumber raita occasionally."]},"evening_snack":{"dish_name":"Steamed Beetroot and Carrot with Lemon and Fennel","ingredients":["beetroot 50g, sliced and steamed","carrot 40g, sliced and steamed","ghee 3g","fennel seeds 1/4 tsp, lightly crushed","lemon juice 1 tsp","salt 1 pinch"],"portion":"1 small plate ~120g","macros":{"protein":"2g","carbs":"16g","fat":"3g","calories":"100 kcal"},"why":"Warm, slightly sweet root vegetables with fennel aid digestion and provide grounding before a simple dinner, which supports restful sleep.","substitutions":["Replace beetroot with sweet potato.","Use olive oil instead of ghee if you want a vegan option."]},"dinner":{"dish_name":"Simple Rice Kanji with Moong Dal and Ginger","ingredients":["white rice 60g","split yellow moong dal 25g","water 500ml","ghee 8g","ginger 1/2 tsp, grated","cumin seeds 1/2 tsp","salt to taste","fresh coriander leaves 1 tbsp"],"portion":"1 large bowl ~420g","macros":{"protein":"11g","carbs":"53g","fat":"10g","calories":"360 kcal"},"why":"Very light, soupy kanji is ideal for a Sunday night reset, extremely easy to digest and deeply calming for Vata, setting you up for excellent sleep.","substitutions":["Replace rice with broken wheat for more fiber if desired.","Skip dal for an ultra-light plain rice kanji when you feel heavy."]}}}]}
